   <body>
      <prereq>
         <ul>
            <li>Departments are already  defined. <ph product="Exclude_PG_Content">For information on departments, refer to<xref href="CrtDept.xml">Creating a Department</xref>.</ph>
            </li>
         </ul>
      </prereq>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>In the module menu, click <uicontrol>Library</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>The <uicontrol>LIBRARY MANAGEMENT</uicontrol> page is displayed.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the navigation pane, expand <uicontrol>Planning</uicontrol>,and then click <uicontrol>ScoringCategory</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>The <uicontrol>SCORING CATEGORY </uicontrol>list page is displayed.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click <uicontrol>New</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>The new <uicontrol>SCORING CATEGORY </uicontrol>page is displayed.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the<uicontrol>Name</uicontrol> box, enter the name of the scoring category.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the<uicontrol>Description</uicontrol> box, enter the description for the scoring category.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>From the <uicontrol>Department</uicontrol> drop-down list, select the department to associate the category with.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the <uicontrol>Weightage (%)</uicontrol> field, enter the required department weightage.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Optionally, to mark the category as inactive, clear the <uicontrol>Is Active</uicontrol> check box.</p>
            <p> Inactive categories are not available for selection in the <uicontrol>Criteria </uicontrol>catalog.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>
               <ph href="../../../../Warehouse/Task_Warehouse/Save_Options.xml#task-9654/SaveRecord"/>
            </p>
         </li>
      </ol>
